verblex: 1. To eat the main meal of the day, especially when that meal is in the middle of the day. English = have dinner.
2. To eat a meal as part of a formal social event in the evening. English = dine.
3. To put something into your mouth, chew it, and swallow it. English = eat.
nomlex: 1. The main meal of the day, especially when that meal is in the middle of the day. English = dinner.
2. A formal social event in the evening at which a meal is served. English = dinner.
3. An occasion when people eat. English = meal.
4. Anything which you can eat. English = food.
